Dear Sarah,

I wanted to provide you with a status update on the Pinnacle litigation as we approach the one-month mark since filing.

The complaint was filed on August 15, and Pinnacle was served on August 22. Pinnacle has retained Morrison & Lee LLP as defense counsel, with Jennifer Walsh's team handling the matter. This is a well-regarded patent litigation firm, so we should expect competent and aggressive defense tactics, but nothing that changes our fundamental assessment of the case.

Pinnacle's answer is due on September 19. We anticipate they will assert counterclaims for declaratory judgment of non-infringement and invalidity, which is standard. We are monitoring for any antitrust counterclaims related to the licensing relationship, though we assess that risk as low.

The initial case management conference is scheduled for October 6 before Judge Strauss. We are preparing our proposed case management plan, which will include our position on the scheduling order. We intend to propose:

- Claim construction briefing: December 2025 - January 2026
- Markman hearing: Late January or early February 2026
- Fact discovery cutoff: May 2026
- Expert discovery: May - July 2026
- Dispositive motion deadline: August 2026
- Trial: October or November 2026

I have also begun the process of identifying and vetting expert witnesses. For our technical infringement expert, I am recommending Dr. Robert Patel from Stanford, who has excellent credentials in thermal compression molding technology and has testified in several patent cases. For patent validity, I recommend Dr. Emily Nakamura from Caltech, who is widely regarded as one of the top experts in composite materials processing. I will send you their CVs and proposed engagement terms this week.

One additional item: we received a letter from Pinnacle's counsel last Friday requesting a meet-and-confer regarding the scope of the litigation hold. This is routine, and Daniel will handle the call. We do not anticipate any issues.

Please let me know if you have any questions or if there are any developments on Meridian's end that we should be aware of.

Best regards,
Rachel M. Torres
